[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Build the Feature Table
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m With hourly counts as the target, the feature table joins in calendar features, weather data, flu surveillance, lag features, and event flags. This is where most of the modeling value is created. A model with great hyperparameters and bad features will be beaten by an average model with good features every time. The feature table is the input to both training and inference; building it once and reusing it avoids skew between the two.
