[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "The Python companion implements the full ED arrival forecasting recipe end-to-end across the five pseudocode steps (hourly aggregation, feature build, volume+acuity training, forecast composition with prediction intervals, and DynamoDB load with CURRENT pointers). boto3 usage is correct: clients/resource are constructed with proper service names (s3, dynamodb, events, cloudwatch, sagemaker-runtime, kinesis), an adaptive retry Config is applied, and the API call shapes used by the mocks mirror real boto3 signatures (batch_writer/put_item with Item=, put_events with Entries=, put_metric_data with Namespace/MetricData). Error handling is addressed via extensive comments on retries, UnprocessedItems, late-record reconciliation, Decimal conversion for DynamoDB float rejection, KMS, deploy-time guardrail asserts on resource names, and PHI/HIPAA logging discipline. Implementations are concrete rather than stubs: the synthetic ADT generator, Poisson volume model with stratified means and residual sigma for prediction intervals, multinomial acuity mix model with stratified shares and log-loss evaluation, future feature builder, forecast composer, and DynamoDB loader all contain working logic, with mocks clearly labeled as in-process stand-ins to keep the demo runnable while production swaps documented in the Gap to Production section."}[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h